{
  "texts": [
    "Demonstrating adeptness in planning, reasoning, decision-making (Wei et al., 2022a), LLMs propel the development of intelligent agents (Wooldridge and Jennings, 1995; Maes, 1995).",
    "Early endeavors (Yao et al., 2023; Shinn et al., 2023) established framework prototypes of LLM agents, and explored LLM capability in tool learning (Schick et al., 2023) and environment interaction (Yao et al., 2022; Zhou et al., 2023a).",
    "Empowered by GPT-4, capable LLM agents such as AutoGPT (Richards, 2023), and Voyager (Wang et al., 2023a), can autonomously complete user instructions.",
    "With col-laboration of agents, multi-agents (Hong et al., 2023; Qian et al., 2023; Xu et al., 2023b) have shown abilities in solving increasingly complex tasks.",
    "While the research community focuses mainly on developing more capable LLM agents in more scenarios (Team, 2023; Xie et al., 2023), safety of LLM agents remains an open challenge."
  ]
}